+# Projects And Workflow Research Index
+
+This folder collects the documentation derived from the Projects discussion and the new Workflow-centered architecture direction.
+
+## Goal
+
+The goal of this research is to design Pibo's own lightweight Workflow model for Projects and future agent orchestration.
+
+The target direction is:
+
+```text
+Workflow = central process, state, graph, runtime, and tracing unit
+Session = interaction or run context inside a Workflow
+Project = project context that groups workflow-driven work
+Personal Chat = default room for lightweight chat/minimal workflows
+```
+
+For Projects, this means we are no longer treating Sessions as the primary logic unit. A Project contains Workflow Runs and their Sessions. The Workflow owns the state machine, graph, process logic, dataflow, runtime orchestration, and workflow-level tracing.
+
+## Core Project Specs
+
+- [`../../spec/projects/spec-architecture-workflow-engine.md`](../../spec/projects/spec-architecture-workflow-engine.md)  
+  General Workflow architecture: Workflow as state machine, graph, runtime model, process model, and extensible execution unit.
+
+- [`../../spec/projects/spec-product-projects-area.md`](../../spec/projects/spec-product-projects-area.md)  
+  Projects product spec under the new Workflow model: Projects, Personal Chat, Workflow-backed Sessions, Standard Project Workflow, future Research Workflow, session worktrees, Docker workers, and tracing.
+
+- [`../../spec/projects/index.md`](../../spec/projects/index.md)  
+  Spec-side index for the Projects and Workflow specs.
+
+## Research Docs
+
+- [`workflow-framework-research-plan.md`](workflow-framework-research-plan.md)  
+  Research plan for evaluating workflow, graph, state-machine, durable workflow, and multi-agent orchestration frameworks.
+
+- [`workflow-framework-first-assessment-2026-05-07.md`](workflow-framework-first-assessment-2026-05-07.md)  
+  First assessment after web research and cloning relevant projects. Current recommendation: use external projects as references and build a small Pibo-native Workflow MVP.
+
+- [`workflow-framework-assessments-2026-05-07/`](workflow-framework-assessments-2026-05-07/)  
+  Detailed subagent assessments for the twelve cloned reference projects, preserved as reference material for Pibo's Workflow MVP design.
+
+## Cloned Reference Projects
+
+The following reference projects were cloned under `~/code` for research:
+
+| Project | Local path | Current research role |
+| --- | --- | --- |
+| LangGraph.js | `~/code/langgraphjs` | Agent workflow/orchestration reference |
+| XState | `~/code/xstate` | State-machine/statechart semantics reference |
+| Graphlib | `~/code/graphlib` | Low-level graph data structure reference |
+| Graphology | `~/code/graphology` | Graph API, events, and algorithms reference |
+| ts-edge | `~/code/ts-edge` | Lightweight TypeScript graph workflow reference |
+| Robot3 | `~/code/robot` | Minimal functional FSM reference |
+| Matchina | `~/code/matchina` | Lightweight TypeScript state-machine reference |
+| FicusJS | `~/code/ficusjs` | Lightweight FSM reference |
+| OpenWorkflow | `~/code/openworkflow` | Durable/resumable workflow reference |
+| DBOS Transact TS | `~/code/dbos-transact-ts` | Durable workflow/checkpointing reference |
+| LlamaIndex Workflows TS | `~/code/workflows-ts` | Event-workflow reference; noted as deprecated |
+| SocietyAI | `~/code/societyai` | TypeScript multi-agent graph and observability reference |
+
+## Current Architectural Direction
+
+Do not adopt a framework yet.
+
+Use the cloned projects to inform a Pibo-owned design:
+
+```text
+LangGraph.js for agent graph concepts
++ XState/Robot/Matchina for state-machine ideas
++ Graphlib/Graphology for graph modeling ideas
++ OpenWorkflow/DBOS for durability ideas
++ Pibo-native Workflow implementation as target
+```
+
+The first implementation should stay small and align with Pibo's own boundaries:
+
+- Pibo Sessions as interaction/run contexts.
+- Workflow Runs as process instances.
+- Workflow definitions as product/plugin-owned units.
+- Explicit node and transition trace events.
+- Local persistence first.
+- Standard Project Workflow first.
+- Future agent-callable workflows.
+- Future PyHosted runtime nodes.
+
+## Related Shared Vocabulary
+
+`GLOSSARY.md` defines the shared vocabulary for:
+
+- Workflow
+- Workflow Run
+- Workflow Type
+- Workflow Usage
+- Workflow Node
+- Workflow Transition
+- Workflow Trace
+- Pibo Project
+
+Keep this index, the specs, and the glossary aligned when the Projects/Workflow model changes.
