+# Workflow Framework Reference Assessments
+
+Date: 2026-05-07
+
+This folder preserves the twelve subagent research reports created for Pibo's Workflow MVP design. The reports inspect local clones under `~/code` and evaluate which ideas can inform a small Pibo-native Workflow layer.
+
+These documents are research notes, not dependency approval and not legal review. Use them to understand useful concepts, mismatches, and cleanroom borrowing candidates. Do not copy third-party source code into Pibo without explicit approval.
+
+## Context
+
+The Pibo specs point to a Pibo-native Workflow layer:
+
+```text
+Workflow = process logic, state machine, graph execution, runtime orchestration, dataflow, tracing
+Session = interaction or runtime context inside a Workflow Run
+Project = project context that groups workflow-driven work
+```
+
+The assessments support the current architecture direction: keep the Workflow engine Pibo-owned, reference external projects for ideas, and avoid adopting a third-party framework as the V1 core.
+
+## Reports
+
+| Project | Report | Role |
+| --- | --- | --- |
+| LangGraph.js | [`langgraphjs.md`](langgraphjs.md) | Primary agent graph/orchestration reference |
+| XState | [`xstate.md`](xstate.md) | Statechart and transition semantics reference |
+| ts-edge | [`ts-edge.md`](ts-edge.md) | Lightweight typed graph workflow API reference |
+| Graphlib | [`graphlib.md`](graphlib.md) | Low-level graph data and algorithm reference |
+| Graphology | [`graphology.md`](graphology.md) | Graph API, attributes, events, and algorithms reference |
+| Robot3 | [`robot3.md`](robot3.md) | Minimal functional FSM reference |
+| Matchina | [`matchina.md`](matchina.md) | TypeScript-first lightweight FSM reference |
+| FicusJS | [`ficusjs.md`](ficusjs.md) | Low-priority FSM API reference |
+| OpenWorkflow | [`openworkflow.md`](openworkflow.md) | Durable and resumable workflow reference |
+| DBOS Transact TS | [`dbos-transact-ts.md`](dbos-transact-ts.md) | Durable execution and checkpointing reference |
+| LlamaIndex Workflows TS | [`workflows-ts.md`](workflows-ts.md) | Deprecated event-workflow reference |
+| SocietyAI | [`societyai.md`](societyai.md) | Multi-agent graph and observability reference |
+
+## Common Template
+
+Each report uses this structure:
+
+1. Metadata
+2. One-line Verdict
+3. What Problem It Solves
+4. Core Abstractions Observed
+5. Fit Against Pibo Requirements
+6. Useful Concepts For Pibo
+7. Mismatches And Risks
+8. Minimal Pibo-Native Borrowing Candidates
+9. Open Questions / Follow-up Files
+10. Recommendation
+
+## Cross-Project Takeaways
+
+- **Core engine:** Build Pibo-native. None of the assessed projects cleanly owns Pibo's full boundary: Workflow Runs, Pibo Sessions, Projects, worker/worktree isolation, usage modes, and Chat Web trace integration.
+- **Graph model:** Use LangGraph.js, ts-edge, Graphlib, Graphology, and SocietyAI as references for node/edge definitions, conditional routing, graph validation, and multi-agent graphs.
+- **State machine:** Use XState, Robot3, and Matchina as references for events, guards, actions, state snapshots, ordered transitions, and explicit transition outcomes.
+- **Durability:** Use OpenWorkflow and DBOS as references for checkpointing, retry, resume, wait/signal, and durable run identity.
+- **Observability:** Combine SocietyAI/LangGraph-style execution events with Pibo's Workflow Trace schema: node start/complete/fail, state before/after, transition decision, runtime/session correlation, retries, feedback, cleanup.
+- **Adoption stance:** Treat all projects as reference-only for V1. Draft neutral Pibo-owned specs before implementation.
+
