+# Implementation Plan: Workflow MVP And Projects Tab
+
+## 1. Goal
+
+Build the Workflow MVP as a new Projects experience without breaking the current Sessions experience.
+
+The Sessions tab stays available and keeps its current behavior. The new Projects tab starts as a controlled copy of the Sessions experience, then replaces Room language with Project language and adds Workflow Runs, Workflow state, Workflow Trace events, and Standard Project Workflow actions.
+
+The implementation should use a strangler approach:
+
+```text
+Sessions tab: current Rooms + Sessions behavior stays intact
+Projects tab: copied Sessions UX + Project language + Workflow system
+```
+
+This keeps Pibo usable while the Workflow system grows.
+
+## 2. Non-negotiable Constraints
+
+- Do not remove the Sessions tab in this implementation cycle.
+- Do not rename existing Sessions routes or APIs in a way that breaks current work.
+- Do not move process state into Sessions. Workflow state lives on Workflow Runs.
+- Do not add a third-party workflow framework as a core dependency.
+- Do not run execution-capable project work in the host checkout. Use existing isolated workspace and Docker worker systems when runtime nodes reach that stage.
+- Do not make destructive cleanup automatic. Require explicit user confirmation.
+
+## 3. Target User Experience
+
+### 3.1 Navigation
+
+Chat Web should expose both tabs:
+
+```text
+Sessions | Projects | Agents | Context | Settings
+```
+
+Sessions remains the stable fallback. Projects is the new Workflow-backed product surface.
+
+### 3.2 Sessions Tab
+
+The Sessions tab keeps current behavior:
+
+- current room/session navigation,
+- current room CRUD,
+- current session CRUD,
+- current composer,
+- current runtime trace views,
+- current archived room/session behavior.
+
+Only safe shared-component extraction should touch Sessions.
+
+### 3.3 Projects Tab
+
+The Projects tab begins as a copy of the Sessions layout:
+
+- left sidebar lists Projects instead of Rooms,
+- main panel shows Project Sessions or the active Workflow Run,
+- existing session transcript and runtime trace surfaces are reused,
+- labels say Project, Project Session, Workflow Run, and Workflow Trace where appropriate.
+
+The first Projects version can be simple. It must show Workflow state and keep links to the underlying Pibo Session trace.
+
+### 3.4 Standard Project Workflow
+
+New project work should create or attach to a `standard-project` Workflow Run.
+
+Initial flow:
+
+```text
+spec -> implementation -> execution -> test -> loop -> user_feedback -> system_update -> completed
+                                      \-> failed
+user_feedback --request_changes--> implementation
+user_feedback --discard--> discarded
+```
+
+The first version may run a skeleton flow before runtime-backed implementation is complete, as long as every state transition and trace event persists.
+
+## 4. Architecture Slices
+
+### 4.1 Product Surface Slice
+
+Add Projects as a new Chat Web area while preserving Sessions.
+
+Primary files likely involved:
+
+- `src/apps/chat-ui/src/main.tsx`
+- `src/apps/chat-ui/src/App.tsx`
+- `src/apps/chat-ui/src/api.ts`
+- `src/apps/chat-ui/src/types.ts`
+- `src/apps/chat-ui/src/styles.css`
+- future extracted components under `src/apps/chat-ui/src/projects/` and `src/apps/chat-ui/src/sessions/`
+
+### 4.2 Workflow Core Slice
+
+Add the Pibo-owned Workflow engine foundation.
+
+Likely new backend modules:
+
+- `src/workflows/types.ts`
+- `src/workflows/registry.ts`
+- `src/workflows/validation.ts`
+- `src/workflows/store.ts`
+- `src/workflows/runner.ts`
+- `src/workflows/trace.ts`
+- `src/workflows/standard-project.ts`
+
+### 4.3 Projects Backend Slice
+
+Add a Project-facing backend surface. It may initially wrap existing Room storage, but the public API and UI language should use Project terms.
+
+Likely modules:
+
+- `src/apps/chat/projects.ts` or `src/projects/store.ts`
+- new project endpoints in `src/apps/chat/web-app.ts`
+- project serialization helpers for Chat Web bootstrap/read models
+
+Compatibility option for the first slice:
+
+```text
+PiboProject API -> existing PiboRoomStore row with project metadata marker
+```
+
+This avoids a risky migration while Projects UI and Workflows stabilize. A later slice can introduce a dedicated `pibo_projects` table if needed.
+
+### 4.4 Workflow Read Model Slice
+
+Expose Workflow Runs and Workflow Trace state to Chat Web.
+
+Likely API endpoints:
+
+```text
+GET    /api/chat/projects/bootstrap
+GET    /api/chat/projects
+POST   /api/chat/projects
+GET    /api/chat/projects/:projectId
+PATCH  /api/chat/projects/:projectId
+POST   /api/chat/projects/:projectId/workflows
+GET    /api/chat/workflows/:workflowRunId
+GET    /api/chat/workflows/:workflowRunId/trace
+POST   /api/chat/workflows/:workflowRunId/resume
+POST   /api/chat/workflows/:workflowRunId/discard
+```
+
+Endpoint names can change during implementation, but the product boundary should stay Project/Workflow-oriented.
+
+## 5. Work Package Dependency Graph
+
+```text
+WP0 Baseline inventory and contracts
+  -> WP1 Workflow contracts and validation
+  -> WP2 Workflow persistence
+  -> WP3 Project API facade
+  -> WP4 Projects tab shell
+
+WP1 + WP2 -> WP5 Function/user-node runner
+WP2 + WP3 -> WP6 Workflow read model APIs
+WP4 + WP6 -> WP7 Projects UI workflow status
+WP5 + WP6 -> WP8 standard-project skeleton
+WP8 + existing Session Router -> WP9 runtime node adapter
+WP7 + WP8 -> WP10 user feedback actions
+WP9 + WP10 -> WP11 end-to-end hardening
+```
+
+## 6. Work Packages
